Celebrate the official opening of the new look Mitchelton Library with Alison Alexander.
 
 Citrus fruits are versatile in the kitchen and can be used&nbsp;in savoury and sweet dishes. Taste some great recipes as&nbsp;food consultant Alison Alexander talks about how to use&nbsp;these readily available winter fruits in the kitchen.
 
 
 Participants will receive a collection of delicious recipes to try at home. &nbsp;

Celebrate the official opening of the new look Mitchelton Library with&nbsp;recycled craft activities for children&nbsp;in the library.
 
 Hosted by Bec Hollis and Ellie Beck, children can weave on a loom and decorate woolen snowflakes using recycled yarn. Children will be encouraged to help decorate the community citrus garden by displaying their creations along the fence of the garden at the front entrance to Mitchelton Library.
 
 Children can join the fun at any stage throughout the morning.&nbsp;&nbsp;
